<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Notes on writing and process</title><link>https://blog.matthewdelhey.com/</link><description>Recent content on Notes on writing and process</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Wed, 02 Mar 2022 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://blog.matthewdelhey.com/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Blogging with org-mode and hugo (part 1)</title><link>https://blog.matthewdelhey.com/posts/blog-setup-1/</link><pubDate>Wed, 02 Mar 2022 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://blog.matthewdelhey.com/posts/blog-setup-1/</guid><description>
&lt;p>
Here&amp;#39;s how I setup a simple blog using &lt;a href="https://orgmode.org">org-mode&lt;/a> (because great), &lt;a href="https://pages.github.com">github-pages&lt;/a> (because free), and &lt;a href="https://gohugo.io">hugo&lt;/a> (because convenient). This is somewhat involved, so I&amp;#39;ve split it up into two parts. In the first part, we&amp;#39;ll just get an html page up and running. In the second part, we&amp;#39;ll configure hugo.&lt;/p>
&lt;div id="outline-container-headline-1" class="outline-2">
&lt;h2 id="headline-1">
1. Initiate.
&lt;/h2>
&lt;div id="outline-text-headline-1" class="outline-text-2">
&lt;p>Initiate a new project on &lt;a href="https://github.com/new">github.com/new&lt;/a>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>
&lt;img src="https://blog.matthewdelhey.com/blog-setup-1/1.png" alt="/blog-setup-1/1.png" title="/blog-setup-1/1.png" />&lt;/p>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>
&lt;div id="outline-container-headline-2" class="outline-2">
&lt;h2 id="headline-2">
2. Clone.
&lt;/h2>
&lt;div id="outline-text-headline-2" class="outline-text-2">
&lt;p>Now, clone the repository on your machine. Replace with your repo name.&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="src src-bash">
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>git clone https://github.com/mdelhey/blog.matthewdelhey.com.git
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>cd blog.matthewdelhey.com&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>
&lt;div id="outline-container-headline-3" class="outline-2">
&lt;h2 id="headline-3">
3. Commit.
&lt;/h2>
&lt;div id="outline-text-headline-3" class="outline-text-2">
&lt;p>Make our first commit. For now, we&amp;#39;ll stick with a test HTML page.&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="src src-bash">
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>touch index.html
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>echo &lt;span style="color:#e6db74">&amp;#34;TEST PAGE&amp;#34;&lt;/span> &amp;gt; index.html
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>git add -A
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>git commit -m &lt;span style="color:#e6db74">&amp;#39;first commit&amp;#39;&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>git push&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>
&lt;div id="outline-container-headline-4" class="outline-2">
&lt;h2 id="headline-4">
4. Github pages.
&lt;/h2>
&lt;div id="outline-text-headline-4" class="outline-text-2">
&lt;p>&lt;em>Do not add a CNAME file&lt;/em>, as this will interfere with the DNS registration. Check &lt;code class="verbatim">Enforce HTTPS&lt;/code>.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>
&lt;img src="https://blog.matthewdelhey.com/blog-setup-1/2.png" alt="/blog-setup-1/2.png" title="/blog-setup-1/2.png" />&lt;/p>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>
&lt;div id="outline-container-headline-5" class="outline-2">
&lt;h2 id="headline-5">
5. DNS.
&lt;/h2>
&lt;div id="outline-text-headline-5" class="outline-text-2">
&lt;p>We need to setup DNS next. This can be kind of tricky. Here&amp;#39;s what my DNS settings on Namecheap looks like. (I&amp;#39;m using a subdomain for this blog.)&lt;/p>
&lt;p>
&lt;img src="https://blog.matthewdelhey.com/blog-setup-1/3.png" alt="/blog-setup-1/3.png" title="/blog-setup-1/3.png" />&lt;/p>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>
&lt;div id="outline-container-headline-6" class="outline-2">
&lt;h2 id="headline-6">
6. Test.
&lt;/h2>
&lt;div id="outline-text-headline-6" class="outline-text-2">
&lt;p>Pray to the DNS gods until you see your test page.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>
&lt;img src="https://blog.matthewdelhey.com/blog-setup-1/4.png" alt="/blog-setup-1/4.png" title="/blog-setup-1/4.png" />&lt;/p>
&lt;/div>
